    <div id="editing">
      <div id="help">
        <h2>Syntax</h2>
        <p>
          The syntax is composed of groups of one or two lines delimited by an empty line.
        </p>

        <p>
          1. When there are two lines, the top row is for chords and bottom row for
          lyrics. When there are two lines the lines are aligned on matching spaces.
        </p>
        
        <p>      
          A pipe character (|) has a special meaning. When pipe characters align, a vertical bar is displayed in their place.
        </p>
        
        <pre>
          | F                 | Em              | G        |
          This- _ | time I have real- | ly led my-self- | _ astray |
        </pre>

        <p>
          When the group has only one line, it is shown as is except when it's one of the following pragmas.
        </p>
        <pre>
          (no drums)
        </pre>
        
        <p>
          <code>#song <i>Song name</i></code><br/>
          Set the title of the song.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          <code>#section <i>Section name</i></code><br/>
          Start a new section, for example verse or chorus. Lines of a section are kept together when possible. Section ends when another begins or at the end of text.
        </p>

        <p>      
          See <a href="examples.html">examples</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <button id="save-button">Save</button>
